</div>
</div>
<p><b>Veronica Esposito</b> is an associate marriage and family therapist specializing in serving transgender individuals; the “<a href="https://www.worldliteraturetoday.org/author/veronica-esposito">Untranslatable</a>” columnist for <em>WLT</em> since 2023; and a regular contributor to venues including <i>The Guardian, Xtra Magazine</i>, and San Francisco NPR affiliate KQED. She was a judge for the 2022 National Book Award in Translation.</p>
